ution completes.\n\nReal environment tested: local focused Vitest through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`, local focused lint/format checks, local autoreview, synthetic/private-name scrub, and AWS Crabbox Linux `pnpm check:changed` on the previous rebased branch head. Blacksmith Testbox was unavailable in this shell because `blacksmith auth login` is required.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n- Force-pushed branch head `cec1f1867e2a598701a298428335ea60ae51cdc3`, rebased onto `origin/main` `598e3f8e7bb789fa54527b6cc5ea166c4ddb818a`.\n- Latest focused Plugin SDK host-hook proof: `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- Latest focused format/lint/diff checks: `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/plugins/registry.ts src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts`, `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/plugins/registry.ts src/plugins/contracts/host-hooks.contract.test.ts`, and `git diff --check`.\n- Local review for the new host-hook metadata slice: `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\n- AWS Crabbox changed gate before the final rebase: `CRABBOX_AWS_REGION=us-east-1 CRABBOX_CAPACITY_REGIONS=us-east-1,us-east-2,us-west-2,eu-west-1,eu-central-1 node scripts/crabbox-wrapper.mjs run --provider aws --shell -- \"corepack pnpm check:changed\"`\n- Changed-file and PR/spec scrub for the reported plugin name and private path patterns.\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n- Focused Plugin SDK host-hook proof passed after final rebase: 1 file, 51 tests passed.\n- Focused oxfmt check, targeted oxlint, and `git diff --check` passed for the host-hook metadata slice.\n- Autoreview for the host-hook metadata slice was clean with no accepted/actionable findings.\n- AWS Crabbox `check:changed` on provider `aws`, lease `cbx_e514654528c4`, run `run_5a6a15bc6d4e`, passed guard checks plus core/core-test/extensions/extension-test typecheck, then failed `lint core` on `src/commands/agent-via-gateway.ts`.\n- `src/commands/agent-via-gateway.ts` is unchanged between this branch and latest `origin/main`; the lint failure is existing main drift from commit `ec0d3752ca6` adding `__testing`.\n- Current branch diff, local spec, and PR body scrub pass for the reported plugin name and private paths.\n\nObserved result after fix:\n\n- Synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures with unreadable names, schemas, descriptions, approval fields, provider metadata, MCP catalog fields, cached runtime descriptors, Codex dynamic-tool descriptors, MCP argument preparers, and Plugin SDK tool metadata no longer crash the relevant projection/resolution/registration paths.\n- Healthy siblings, such as `mockplugin_status`, `mockplugin_store`, and a `mockplugin-status` command registration, continue through materialization, descriptor caching, provider payload conversion, MCP/Gateway listing, agent-core validation, Codex dynamic-tool bridge registration, plugin-tools MCP execution, and plugin host-hook registration while malformed siblings are omitted, quarantined, or diagnosed.\n- Plugin tool metadata registration now stores a sanitized metadata record from bounded field reads instead of spreading the plugin-provided object.\n\nWhat was not tested:\n\n- Blacksmith Testbox `pnpm check:changed` was not run because `blacksmith` is not authenticated in this shell.\n- AWS Crabbox `check:changed` was not rerun after the final rebase because latest `origin/main` still contains the unchanged `src/commands/agent-via-gateway.ts` lint failure; rerunning would reproduce that same unrelated main drift.\n- GitHub CI for the newest force-push is still running/pending.\n- No live third-party plugin was referenced or exercised; tests intentionally use synthetic `fuzzplugin`/`mockplugin` fixtures.\n\n## Current review state\n\n- PR remains draft while this fuzzing/hardening lane continues.\n- Latest pushed commit: `cec1f1867e2a598701a298428335ea60ae51cdc3` (`fix(plugins): guard tool metadata registration`).\n",
